            "creation_date": 1361309738,
            "body": "<blockquote>\n  <p>JavaScipt can't access the iframe's DOM as it is on a separate server, but the applet can...<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>In think Andrew had the right idea.  JS can access content on other servers <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5943630/basic-example-of-using-ajax-with-jsonp\">using JSONP<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n<p>To communicate with cross-domain iframes, you may need to look into something like <a href=\"http://ternarylabs.github.com/porthole/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Porthole<\/a> as well.<\/p>\n",
